// Flush ensures that all messages handed to the Send* methods have been
// delivered to the broker.
//
// This producer uses segmentio/kafka-go in its default synchronous mode
// (Writer.Async == false), so every Send* call only returns after the broker
// has acknowledged the message and there is nothing buffered on the client to
// drain. Flush is therefore a no-op provided for parity with the other
// language SDKs; it only reports context cancellation. Resilient delivery is
